      "content": "When critics mention bureaucratic bloat, they are often referring to the immense administrative overhead required to manage a single-payer or heavily regulated system, which can slow down decision-making. The moral difference is profoundly tied to whether one prioritizes collective security over individual economic freedom. Ultimately, the \"correct\" side depends on whether you value guaranteed baseline security above all else or prioritize market-driven efficiency.",
